# Code Quality

## Style

- async/await for asynchronous operations
- JSDoc on public methods
- Use `this.log.*` — never `console.log`
- Tabs, single quotes (see `prettier.config.mjs`)
- ESLint via `@iobroker/eslint-config` — run `npm run lint` before commit

## Resource cleanup

Clear timers in `onUnload()` via `this.clearInterval()` and always call `callback()`:

```javascript
this.scanInterval = this.setInterval(async () => { /* ... */ }, intervalMs);

onUnload(callback) {
  try {
    if (this.scanInterval) {
      this.clearInterval(this.scanInterval);
      this.scanInterval = undefined;
    }
    callback();
  } catch (error) {
    this.log.error(`Error during unloading: ${error.message}`);
    callback();
  }
}
```

Use `this.setInterval()` / `this.clearInterval()` — not plain `setInterval()` / `clearInterval()` (adapter checker W5004).

## Error handling

- Wrap scan/async work in try/catch; log errors, do not crash the adapter
- Use adapter log levels: error, warn, info, debug
- Prefer native `fetch` (Node 22+) over axios for HTTP

## Dependencies

- Use `npm ci` in CI; commit `package-lock.json` with `package.json`
- Prefer `@iobroker/adapter-core`; avoid deprecated packages
- Update dependencies in separate PRs only
